# Project core

## Secrets and env

- Never commit `.env` or real `BOT_TOKEN` / chat IDs. Use `.env.example` as the template only.
- Config is loaded in `config.py` via `python-dotenv`; `validate_config()` runs at bot startup.

## Changes

- Make the smallest diff that solves the task. Do not refactor unrelated code or rename symbols without need.
- Match existing style: `from __future__ import annotations`, type hints, pathlib for paths.

## User-facing language

- Telegram replies and any other text sent to users via the bot must be **English**. Keep them English unless the user explicitly asks for another language.

## Layout

- Bot wiring: `bot/main.py`, handlers in `bot/handlers.py`.
- Queue and state: `orchestrator.py`, `state_store.py`, `data/content.json`, queue state file (default `data/state.json`; env **`QUEUE_STATE_PATH`** on Railway + volume — see `docs/RUNBOOK.md`).
- Optional X (Twitter) mirror for **`photo`** queue items only: [`x_poster.py`](../../x_poster.py) — env and behavior in [docs/RUNBOOK.md](../../docs/RUNBOOK.md), [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md).

## Social content and manifest (scale)

- **Authoring:** [web/public/posts.json](../../web/public/posts.json) and [data/polls.json](../../data/polls.json). PNGs: [web/public/images/posts/](../../web/public/images/posts/) (UI) and [data/images/](../../data/images/) (mirror). Counts are **not** the old “~30 posts” archive—use `python scripts/audit_posts_png_quizzes.py` for ground truth.
- **Regenerate the bot queue:** `python scripts/sync_queue_from_posts.py --in-place` writes [data/content.json](../../data/content.json). Default (no flag) writes gitignored `data/content.generated.json`. Logic: [queue_manifest_sync.py](../../queue_manifest_sync.py).
- **Docs:** [docs/QUEUE_SYNC.md](../../docs/QUEUE_SYNC.md), [docs/CONTENT_INVENTORY.md](../../docs/CONTENT_INVENTORY.md), [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) “Content pipeline”.

## Quality assurance

- After meaningful Python changes, run **`python -m pytest`** from the repo root with dev deps installed ([docs/RUNBOOK.md](../../docs/RUNBOOK.md#running-tests)). CI also runs `python scripts/audit_posts_png_quizzes.py` after pytest.
- After editing [data/polls.json](../../data/polls.json) copy for the web UI, run **`node scripts/sync_polls_to_web.mjs`** (the **web** CI job does this before `npm run build`). Optional local checks: **`python scripts/audit_post_quiz_semantics.py`** (heuristic quiz ↔ post overlap), **`python scripts/rotate_poll_correct_options.py`** when rebalancing binary answer positions ([docs/CURRICULUM_UX_AUDIT.md](../../docs/CURRICULUM_UX_AUDIT.md) §4).
- Regression checklist and invariants: [docs/golden_standard.md](../../docs/golden_standard.md). See **Quality assurance** in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).
